node.text:
Today we mourn the death of Senator Mike Gravel, who passed away this weekend. 

Senator Gravel gave us one of the best debate moments in history, and he truly believed service went beyond the Senate floor, where he is most known for reading the Pentagon Papers on the Senate floor.

In recent years he lent his name to run for President of the United States where volunteers formed what is now the @gravelinstitute, who we proudly support in our shared vision of taking down right wing disinformation with left wing facts and reality.

node.title: Rest in power, Senator Mike Gravel

.
This is about using our collective power to manifest the change that we demand to see in our society."
